"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reviewing code complexities**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking at this code snippet with the suppressed warning for unchecked casts. It looks a bit clunky to me. I wonder if the class cast isn’t real reflection. It might be better to declare a `Function<String, String>` proxy using `limiter.newProxy(target, Function.class, ...)`. I'm considering whether the generic method truly infers T as raw, since it might compile with unchecked conversion. Mentally testing this with `<T> T newProxy(T target, Class<T> interfaceType, ...)`, there's a conflict with T being both `Function<String, String>` and `Function`. It's a bit puzzling!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_poxntl8dXCgWSqmzRRVK0fi8|fc_0bed9c6fb5b7bb6d0169f66c841e5c819ea00ddbdb253d043f\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.google.guava/guava/r06/src/test/java/com_google_guava/guava/SimpleTimeLimiterTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import com.google.common.util.concurrent.SimpleTimeLimiter;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import com.google.common.base.Function;\\nimport com.google.common.util.concurrent.SimpleTimeLimiter;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"            TimedOperation target = new TimedOperation() {\\n                @Override\\n                public String describe(String value) throws InterruptedException {\\n                    return Thread.currentThread().getName() + \\\":\\\" + value;\\n                }\\n            };\\n\\n            TimedOperation proxy = limiter.newProxy(target, TimedOperation.class, 5, TimeUnit.SECONDS);\\n\\n            assertThat(proxy.describe(\\\"payload\\\")).isEqualTo(\\\"simple-time-limiter-worker:payload\\\");\\n\", \"newText\": \"            Function<String, String> target = new Function<String, String>() {\\n                @Override\\n                public String apply(String value) {\\n               