: {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_poxntl8dXCgWSqmzRRVK0fi8|fc_0bed9c6fb5b7bb6d0169f66c841e5c819ea00ddbdb253d043f\", \"toolName\": \"edit\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Successfully replaced 3 block(s) in tests/src/com.google.guava/guava/r06/src/test/java/com_google_guava/guava/SimpleTimeLimiterTest.java.\"}], \"details\": {\"diff\": \"    ...\\n  7 package com_google_guava.guava;\\n  8 \\n  9 import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n 10 \\n+11 import com.google.common.base.Function;\\n 11 import com.google.common.util.concurrent.SimpleTimeLimiter;\\n 12 import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\\n 13 import java.util.concurrent.Executors;\\n 14 import java.util.concurrent.ThreadFactory;\\n    ...\\n 21         ThreadFactory threadFactory = runnable -> new Thread(runnable, \\\"simple-time-limiter-worker\\\");\\n 22         ExecutorService executor = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor(threadFactory);\\n 23         try {\\n 24             SimpleTimeLimiter limiter = new SimpleTimeLimiter(executor);\\n-25             TimedOperation target = new TimedOperation() {\\n+26             Function<String, String> target = new Function<String, String>() {\\n 26                 @Override\\n-27                 public String describe(String value) throws InterruptedException {\\n+28                 public String apply(String value) {\\n 28                     return Thread.currentThread().getName() + \\\":\\\" + value;\\n 29                 }\\n 30             };\\n 31 \\n-32             TimedOperation proxy = limiter.newProxy(target, TimedOperation.class, 5, TimeUnit.SECONDS);\\n+33             Function<String, String> proxy = limiter.newProxy(target, functionInterface(), 5, TimeUnit.SECONDS);\\n 33 \\n-34             assertThat(proxy.describe(\\\"payload\\\")).isEqualTo(\\\"simple-time-limiter-worker:payload\\\");\\n+35             assertThat(proxy.apply(\\\"payload\\\")).isEqualTo(\\\"simple-time-limiter-worker:payload\\\");\\n 35         } finally {\\n 36             executor.shutdownNow();\\n 37             assertThat(executor.awaitTermination(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue();\\n 38         }\\n 39     }\\n 40 \\n-41     public interface TimedOperation {\\n-42         String describe(String value) throws InterruptedException;\\n+42     @SuppressWarnings(\\\"unchecked\\\")\\n+43     private static Class<Function<String, String>> functionInterface() {\\n+44         return (Class<Function<String, String>>) (Class<?>) Function.class;\\n 43     }\\n 44 }\", \"firstChangedLine\": 11}, \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777757318881}}\n3420:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Analyzing metadata and tests**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the final metadata should focus solely on the library. If I add a test that collects proxy config for Function, it might change the metadata generated. The original task didn’t require metadata, maybe just tests? I'm considering that existing metadata lacks proxies. If native tests need metadata, they might fail. It makes sense that the TCK runs the agent to collect metadata from tests and compare it to the repository. This challenge seems to improve dynamic-access coverage since tests collect dynamic accesses, even if they don’t directly interact with repository metadata.\\n\\n**Reviewing code complexities**\\n\\nI'm looking at this code snippet with the suppressed warning for unchecked casts. It looks a bit clunky to me. I wonder if the class cast isn’t real reflection. It might be better to declare a `Function<String, String>` proxy using `limiter.newProxy(target, Function.class, ...)`. I'm considering whether the generic method truly infers T as raw, since it might compile with unchecked conversion. Mentally testing this with `<T> T newProxy(T target, Class<T> interfaceType, ...)`, there's a conflict with T being both `Function<String, String>` and `Function`. It's a bit puzzling!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0bed9c6fb5b7bb6d0169f66c71c4ac819ea73d86d04db474c8\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9myEAMOZtGT0Z30ehcDB4Sua-ajLoXzWklENYu24BGfH4tZXYXdYYybcvuUWW1Cd2j01uDUIfKgi8hpGQDH6M7BlmEvvglAnql-Bb8s0abm2KaTvze3LkZer6rAnH3rLQ7EQ-GXq4rY93zMbbg708nDVYF2Gncp66UyjeU8y0zeN8wS5D6GHgDUoAyrQSokYJMAwJEW3Gjlkf3T8pkaOI9KMZN0UJk6E48sNd8P9_t_ZINv8sa7Ys_HboODI_fQxqF_HSOfOl5-5guY2SSXg037AYd6rczCWlmb1lJgAtBqkFSd61eiBmOmBCKqyikRyiE57ZdOWkRUWhmGUXmhHTa3KvlzSjEpexsCCoQRG7jS9zTEwSDv-3K1Ks4AnlwMFd5IqQWm_VFQYwzCZlrKmOIMLCWLvjg116rN7zc3ejUOeQTif_7JyGnqbjCTHM7QpfkX2F01hn2JJe6bSpDDvdqvts8jdjNLZAN5kMx7wW00kmGFQEScYRroWTPZg-ygTKewmr5pbfRPJXU-4rl0Pb4KAE8XRdifuOD9NbHdtVuI-bn9vElzs4Kii4VxZv3Jv2z7-SOFHG72kjyyNjZcjjqTZhcGWLX90iSxfR1A5yk1_sC8nKuCJ1ibORPFcT51_ie4zHg7T-7ysRWPCJ5qyr2KGJffv3bZ1EYK1HTP1qAq0Naw9OH8fMNAde8ijaecQlTPGVH5wHH5cFKbIvT9PsHQn1W1Ey-9x5ReKzDh0Et-neCXVunZPCpSa-0s7h8-N0ur-v5Fg9Ej2CFzTiybeZjMOYOoM92DTapUapwK8VMcC_UqxYwxfc24CD5c2kF_uFC82a7z3zjfPSHpJAM1t8gHV3hUEICcZVqNWyN62XQFKbIQlbaSjqcNrC6Mymn_88FD8IDV44cHlyBv9odJQ4c3LTyJERbHjIWFUnqc3daETv5FmVuOiCox1r5r_rMNBN2IPTWWlNnzOnGv0kQ6nqcGExO9oJFAAS-vVkWBZbg-JYo8TGdotLklCMSy3tdfvt01s_zEgMiyGCXvLmkB1MBKJux-bOOICKEuAMQMJxeNrQQnvN3g9MdIno7OrwmLiY-S0RwQgJo26jzZlmFaGZJrb89DWaw-jkwVMDVUNrNWazCV_VebZl5FTAJMXeSI-lDZmO1k0KSYgqN-oo8wGNNFarvSksY6Jtm-l8EDHKsg7L_FEVToNmP1-JYlShXJZCryZY0e1RlKG4EItlgila1yf31-g3AyITkMt2BZKfkVyFTYvQs5Es85PHaPl1oS0Ye-4ECg23dV_lTE2ljmqzYumjjYSfvbrnyT3HINl8q4adBqp6qjlUySoshyUB7Ud3el8WSY2nlY8dqatw0AphcqX-6FfdRkm9m2A2hBz53LQDG9o6tcik-HyYHfx9NBsTgOqx1u0AWdqp4PAaUQiupyzknLRXf0g8ZFx94Sq3Wg8uVK2UelCTaS-Dez6U_yjlWilZZYXuM88SphH1S9hGexoXPI4wQR9pVS19qMFoxkxpEa5QLp9W8M3IqiI6wpGbUITqKxkEdu8KYVGZtRXFIEgRPMrKAs_JkwjB6x525IoYaOM8uNVp2glK81Tcwpu9b-rKnX7ExkbnZjPkma9mvEewMqweGC77iuAIjWsSFfeCQzzWyVUteOaxe60vIR88bK8aQAHVrrbWxBycqi9o9Gq0s2RT19TYrVdtobVns6rDThQXJB158bhFrPrlEWykdrEnqFOCfzcyuDPn8rhOAHv82anKnL8QYQExRmibs6OxkJrDlckDwz3BTG5qEhEEWpeuiAOs6qWIMtuC23mKh0rni